text: Jaime Rene Morales Carazo (born 10 September 1936) is a Nicaraguan politician. He was the Vice President of Nicaragua between January 2007 and January 2012.Jaime Morales Carazo juramentado como diputado del Parlacen – LA PRENSA — EL Diario de los Nicaragüenses. Laprensa.com.ni (2012-02-25). Retrieved on 2012-05-09. He was born in Granada, Nicaragua. He was a member of the National Assembly from 2002 until 2007 and again from 2012 until 2017. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1936 births Category:Vice presidents of Nicaragua
title: Jaime Morales Carazo
